dmaw, and the wolf), so I'm down to the last two ; Lodi and the griff. I know where Lodi spawns, but I was just curious, any of you care to throw me some suggestions or tips on this? I'd like to get this done right the first time, and not, for instance, be in the wrong place when the griff decides to make himself known.<br>
<br>
 Thanks in advance.<br>
<br>
 - Ashling Moonshadow -<br>
 - 55'th Scout - <br>
-=Tarew Marr=- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usilvermouse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvermouse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 1:39:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some tips on the Eyepatch :)</span><hr size=1> The griffin spawns a little ways down the hill from the 3 gnomes. Kind of towards the dock. You can sit there hidden np and watch the snow cougars path by every 7 minutes and 40 seconds for 38 hours. have fun!<br>
<br>
Silvermouse <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uashling.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ashling</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 1:55:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some tips on the Eyepatch :)</span><hr size=1> Okay, here's a question. I'm going to be camping Lodi solo, so no druid, ranger, ect... How will I know when Lodi is up, and once I've confirmed that he is up, how do I get him away from the gnolls without getting myself summoned and killed? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaxxel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maxxel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 2:58:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some tips on the Eyepatch :)</span><hr size=1> the gnolls shiver when he pops, also you can see him if you're looking at the water. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umutareneverrest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mutare Neverrest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 3:02:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some tips on the Eyepatch :)</span><hr size=1> or do like i did camp him night and day for weeks upon weeks and lose sleep, while he either skipped spawns, or was rushed by another guild before i could get enough ppl ect, then take a group with you sit there for a couple hours, go afk and come back with lodi munching on you.  =)  lodi is a thorn in the side~<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uviscerspineshank.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Viscer Spineshank</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.silwenae.com/images/topics/cbtag1.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/25/01 11:29:40 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some tips on the Eyepatch :)</span><hr size=1> Lodi......can spawn every 18 hours, can skip spawns.  When he spawns, every gnoll in the area swarms the knoll camp, you'd have 50 knolls in camp.  If your sitting at the gnoll camp looking down at the ice bergs.....you can not miss this fooker....he is as big as the iceberg and falls out of the sky right onto the berg.  He paths straight for the camp and will aggro on you.  If he doesn't aggro, he'll then path south along the water.<br>
<br>
Stormfeather......Can spawn once ever 19 hours.  I have seen him spawn.  If your standing on the pointy tip of land heading off the main land NW...when you can still see  the gnomes sitting under the tree playing dice....stormfeather spawns right up there..you cant miss him.  Best thing to do is get the server pop time....and start counting.  I have heard rumors that he can skip his first cycle frequently. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulimbas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>limbas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/25/01 9:39:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some tips on the Eyepatch :)</span><hr size=1> Spawn time on stormfeather is 19 hours, give or take 15 minutes.  He tends to skip spawns, he skipped two on me, and lemme tell ya how bad that sucked.  Anyway, do not bother with Storm first, get the Lod piece, you will thank yourself later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3138.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3147.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3148.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3148.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.su